tyListDto)\n33-38. Service interfaces (PetService, VisitService, PetTypeService, VetService, SpecialtyService, OwnerViewService)\n\nAll files are complete with their full source code content as displayed above."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5335c7b-0969-4f64-b148-77b8530ff921","uuid":"7430c05b-3c00-4c34-8395-4614247da14a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01HPgnxLFUEy7Yt31BK1s86R","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent. Now I have a complete picture of the application. Let me begin the migration. The strategy is:\n\n1. Replace the Jakarta EE / EJB architecture with Quarkus CDI\n2. Replace `@Stateless` EJB beans with `@ApplicationScoped` CDI beans\n3. Replace `@EJB` injection with `@Inject`\n4. Replace `@PersistenceContext` with `@Inject` for EntityManager\n5. Add `@Transactional` where needed\n6. Create a Quarkus `application.properties`\n7. Create a new `pom.xml` for Quarkus\n8. Update the Dockerfile\n9. Remove JSF/PrimeFaces view layer (not applicable to Quarkus REST-only API)\n\nLet me now write all the migrated files:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":31103,"cache_read_input_tokens":70220,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":31103,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":715},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5335c7b-0969-4f64-b148-77b8530ff921","uuid":"44f8d344-8e56-4cf5-9fd1-4252829d3cc3"}
