hole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/owner/db/OwnerViewServiceImpl.java`\n\n### Key Changes Applied:\n\n1. **Replaced `@Stateless` with `@ApplicationScoped`** - Changed from EJB stateless session beans to CDI application-scoped beans\n2. **Replaced `@EJB` with `@Inject`** - Changed from EJB dependency injection to CDI dependency injection\n3. **Added `@Transactional` to mutating methods** - All methods that create, update, or delete data now have the `@Transactional` annotation for proper transaction management in Quarkus\n4. **Removed `private` modifiers from injected fields** - Changed to package-private access as is standard for CDI injection\n5. **Maintained all existing functionality** - All business logic, lifecycle methods (`@PostConstruct`, `@PreDestroy`), and method signatures remain unchanged\n\nThese changes enable the PetClinic application to run on Quarkus using CDI (Contexts and Dependency Injection) instead of EJB, making it compatible with the Quarkus framework's lightweight, cloud-native architecture."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5335c7b-0969-4f64-b148-77b8530ff921","uuid":"0d512a5c-5d5b-4486-bbc9-bbe28863572d"}
