{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AkAoYR7xu7eZSTf2dacAzr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.vet.api;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import lombok.extern.java.Log;\n     6→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.specialty.Specialty;\n     7→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.specialty.api.SpecialtyEndpointUtil;\n     8→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.specialty.api.SpecialtyListDto;\n     9→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.vet.Vet;\n    10→\n    11→import java.io.Serializable;\n    12→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    13→import java.util.List;\n    14→import java.util.Set;\n    15→\n    16→@Log\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class VetEndpointUtil implements Serializable {\n    19→\n    20→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 607664665910620584L;\n    21→\n    22→    @Inject\n    23→    SpecialtyEndpointUtil specialtyEndpointUtil;\n    24→\n    25→    public VetDto dtoFactory(Vet vet) {\n    26→        VetDto dto = new VetDto();\n    27→        dto.setId(vet.getId());\n    28→        dto.setUuid(vet.getUuid());\n    29→        dto.setFirstName(vet.getFirstName());\n    30→        dto.setLastName(vet.getLastName());\n    31→        Set<Specialty> specialties = vet.getSpecialties();\n    32→        List<Specialty> specialtyList = new ArrayList<>();\n    33→        for (Specialty specialty : specialties) {\n    34→            specialtyList.add(specialty);\n    35→        }\n    36→        SpecialtyListDto specialtyDtoList = this.specialtyEndpointUtil.dtoListFactory(specialtyList);\n    37→        dto.setSpecialtyList(specialtyDtoList);\n    38→        return dto;\n    39→    }\n    40→\n    41→    public VetListDto dtoListFactory(List<Vet> vetList) {\n    42→        List<VetDto> dtoList = new ArrayList<>();\n    43→        for (Vet vet : vetList) {\n    44→            VetDto dto = this.dtoFactory(vet);\n    45→            dtoList.add(dto);\n    46→        }\n    47→        return new VetListDto(dtoList);\n    48→    }\n    49→}\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5335c7b-0969-4f64-b148-77b8530ff921","uuid":"37d30b92-406b-48fa-baef-eda5e7e8007b"}
