n9. Look for any remaining `javax.*` imports\n\nFor each issue found, report:\n- The exact file path\n- The line number\n- The exact error/issue\n- What the fix should be\n\nBe very thorough - read every file that could have an issue."}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":695,"cache_read_input_tokens":60231,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":695,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":627},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b5335c7b-0969-4f64-b148-77b8530ff921","uuid":"d84832ba-e0a2-412e-9c16-8d496fbadc28"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Maven build of a Quarkus application failed with compilation errors. I need you to analyze the build output and identify EVERY compilation error in the MAIN source code (not test code). The build was run in a Docker container at /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output.\n\nRun this command to get the build errors from the most recent Docker build:\n\n```\ndocker build -t test_errors /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__quarkus/run_2/output 2>&1 | grep \"\\[ERROR\\]\" | head -100\n```\n\nIf that doesn't work (because the image is cached), search the build log differently. \n\nActually, let's just look at the source code files directly that had errors. Based on the previous build output, the errors were in these categories:\n\n1. Main source files with errors - read these files to understand the errors:\n   - Files in src/main/java that reference classes/interfaces that may not exist or have wrong imports\n\nSearch for these patterns in the src/main/java directory:\n1. `import.*EJBException` or `import.*EJBTransactionRolledbackException` \n2. Any references to `SelectItem` or `DualListModel` from PrimeFaces\n3. Any references to `FacesConverter` or `Converter`\n4. References to `OwnerViewService` - check if this interface exists and where\n5. References to `OwnerView` interface\n6. Check all view-related classes (anything with \"View\" in the name)\n7. Check for any class that has `implements Serializable` + `@ApplicationScoped` which might cause issues\n8. Check for references to `@Named` beans\n9. Look for any remaining `javax.*` imports\n\nFor each issue found, report:\n- The exact file path\n- The line number\n- The exact error/issue\n- What the fix should be\n\nBe very thorough - read every file that could have an issue."}]},"pare